n=left class=m><span class=title>   Upgrade</span><hr size=1> Warcraft III is one of my new favorite pc games, but I dont think you should upgrade for just that game.  If you dont have enough ram to run it you need to upgrade, considering ram is becoming very important, and sometimes it is better to have alot of ram than a slightly faster clock rate.  Also you should consider upgrading your 3d card considering the new generation of Pc games are going to require high end geforce 3s and low end ge force 4s (newer ATIs are fine also).  I own a newer ge force 4 and it really does help performance. to upgrade to 256 ram ( I reccomend 512 but its not needed) and a low end ge force 4 is going to cost around 210 bucks, based on comp usa prices for IBM ram module for a 256 and Ge force 4 mx420(lowest end Ge force 4)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umelch14.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melch14</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/19/02 3:04:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=343.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thundashock.xoasis.com/zzguy height=110 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Upgrade</span><hr size=1> Thanks, I agree, my computer needs to be upgraded badly. The thing is with upgrading the 3D card, I don't really play many pc games unless there is one that comes along that looks really sweet. I was looking at 3D cards today and I could get a geforce 2 for about 50 bucks which I would be willing to pay, would that work (I think it was a 32 meg)?<br><br>~melch~ <p><i>... and I'm not easily impressed... WOW! a blue car!<i> ~ Homer Simpson<BR> <a href=http://www.geocities.com/melch49><img src="http://thundashock.xoasis.com/hhbanner-medium.jpg"></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umelch14.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melch14</A> at: 8/19/02 3:05:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugekido1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gekido1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/19/02 4:46:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=343.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Upgrade</span><hr size=1> Minimum Requirements<br>400 MHz processor <br>128 MB of RAM <br>16 MB ATI Technologies or nVidia chipset 3D video card <br>700 MB HD space <br>4X CD-ROM drive <br><br>The ge force 2 should do fine for minimum but you will experience some drops in preformace, and ram youll only need to go to 128 which is around maybe 30 bucks? I think that its worth investing a bit more to get better ram but if you play consoles more than pc, and upgradin just for this go mininimum<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uinfinitix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>infiniti x</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/19/02 6:52:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=343.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warcraft 3 *opinions needed*</span><hr size=1> Considering that you may need to upgrade RAM, video card, and harddrive to play Warcraft, u'd prolly be best off just buying a new pc and it'll be a worthwhile investment in the long run.  (tats the cold hard truth).  From adding those 3 components together, ur prolly gonna spent about $400 right off the bat.  <br><br>The voodoo banshee should handle the game alright, but with low RAM and (im assuming) a slower processor, it'd gonna lag and freeze from time to time.  I ran War3 on my old P2-400 PC with a Voodoo3 card and 128 SDRAM, and it works pretty well except when the going gets intense taht i get major slowdown.  <br><br>And you DONT need a geForce3 or 4 to run the game well.  I have a geForce2 Ti card and runs just as fast.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umelch14.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melch14</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/19/02 7:39:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=343.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thundashock.xoasis.com/zzguy height=110 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warcraft 3 *opinions needed*</span><hr size=1> Thanks guys, I appreciate it. Well I'm running on an overclocked PII (at about 700 mhz, I think). If I upgrade my RAM its hopefully gonna be to 256. I don't think I'm gonna upgrade my video card, it suits me just fine for now, and the harddrive is 12 gigs which isn't massive but again, I think it will work for now. I'm hoping with this setup, it should run well. <br><br>~melch~ <p><i>... and I'm not easily impressed... WOW! a blue car!<i> ~ Homer Simpson<BR> <a href=http://www.geocities.com/melch49><img src="http://thundashock.xoasis.com/hhbanner-medium.jpg"></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umelch14.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melch14</A> at: 8/19/02 7:42:31 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=343.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsf